Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g}(chopped into 2cm chunks, no need to peel). Pop them onto
a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, sprinkle over the @dried rosemary{1},
then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat, then spread out in a
single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

== Pesto Baby Leaf Salad ==

Meanwhile, zest and halve the @lemon{½}. Chop the @medium tomato{1}(chopped
into small 1cm pieces). Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a
#garlic press{}).

Put the @fresh pesto{32%g} into a #medium bowl{} and add a squeeze of lemon juice.
Mix in the @olive oil{for the dressing}, then set aside.

== Salmon ==

When the potatoes have 10 mins left, heat a drizzle of oil in a #frying pan{}
on medium-high heat. Pat the @salmon fillets{2} dry with #kitchen paper{} and
season.

Once hot, carefully lay the fish into the pan, skin-side down. Cook for
~{3-4%minutes} before turning over and cooking for ~{2-3%minutes} on the other
side.

> TIP: To get crispy skin on the fish, don't move it around when it's cooking
-> skin-side down.
> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish. It's
-> cooked when opaque in the middle.

When cooked, transfer to a #plate{} to rest and cover with #foil{} to keep warm.

== Warm Tomato Salsa ==

Wipe out your (now empty) frying pan and pop on medium heat with the
@olive oil{for the salsa}. Once hot, add the chopped tomato and cook until just
warmed through, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Gently stir in the garlic and lemon zest and cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.
Squeeze in some lemon juice and season with salt and pepper. Taste and season
again if needed, then remove from the heat.

== To Serve ==

When everything's ready, add the @baby leaf mix{50%g} to your pesto dressing
and toss to coat.

Transfer the salmon to your #plates{} and spoon over the warm tomato salsa.
Serve with the rosemary potatoes and pesto salad alongside. Enjoy!